data.chText: 无特长的；无（需）特别技能的；无（需）专门训练的
data.enText: not having or needing special skills or training

tr: not having or showing or requiring special skill or proficiency
example: unskilled in the art of rhetoric
an enthusiastic but unskillful mountain climber
workers in unskilled occupations are finding fewer and fewer job opportunities

value.def: People who are unskilled do not have any special training for a job.

example.ex: He went to Paris in search of work as an unskilled labourer...
example.tran: 他没有任何劳动技能就到巴黎找起了工作。

example.ex: Most of those who left the province to work abroad were unskilled.
example.tran: 那些离开该省出国打工的人大部分都未经专门训练。

value.tran: 无（特殊）技能的;未经专门训练的

value.def: Unskilled work does not require any special training.

example.ex: In the US, minorities and immigrants have generally gone into low-paid, unskilled jobs.
example.tran: 在美国，少数族裔和移民一般都会从事低薪水、无需特殊技能的工作。

value.tran: 无需(特殊)技能的；不需专门训练的
